article.headline: Cornell 83, New Hampshire 67
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) --Guards Cody Toppert scored 23 points and Ka'Ron Barnes scored 20 to lead Cornell to a 83-67 victory over New Hampshire on Sunday. Cornell (3-3) jumped to a 46-30 lead at halftime by shooting 18-33 from the field, including 7 of 14 on 3-pointers. New Hampshire (2-4) never got much closer. Eric Taylor added 16 points, Gabe Stephenson 10 points and 11 rebounds and Graham Dow 12 points for the Big Red. Ben Sturgill and Ronnie Dennis had 12 points each for New Hampshire.
